In this picture, we were 60ft in the air, traveling from one park to the next. My son was nervous because the car unexpectedly encountered technical difficulties, which caused a pause in forward momentum, at the peak of our journey (no one is exempt from challenges in transition). 

My words couldn’t calm him as the wind rocked us back and forth. So he threw himself into his father’s arms and held on until change came.

Hear me well: traveling with a father who’s not intimidated by your fears is a LUXURY. I’m scared of a generation that will throw away fathers while they’re in turbulent transition.
